# No `private static void` helpers

Never add methods with signature pattern `private static void ...` anywhere in this codebase (main or test).

## Preferred alternatives

- Use an **instance method** (`private void ...`) on the owning class when it is internal logic.
- Extract a **dedicated service/component** when the logic is reusable or non-trivial.
- For mapping logic, prefer **MapStruct** mappers over manual helper methods.

## Rationale

`private static void` helpers tend to hide side effects, make testing harder, and encourage “utility blob” patterns. Prefer dependency-injected, testable collaborators or plain instance methods.

